# Next 16 Best Practices

- Use the App Router conventions already adopted in this repo.
- Use `proxy.ts` for locale routing and edge request rewriting. Do not add new `middleware.ts`.
- Treat `params`, `searchParams`, `headers()`, `cookies()`, and `draftMode()` as async-only APIs in Next 16.
- Use the ESLint CLI with `eslint.config.mjs`; do not add `next lint` back.
- Keep `next.config.js` compatible with Next 16. Avoid reintroducing removed options such as `eslint`, `swcMinify`, or `optimizeFonts`.
- This repo currently relies on custom webpack config. Preserve `--webpack` in scripts unless explicitly migrating to Turbopack.

## Performance

- Mobile-first layouts must avoid decorative backgrounds positioned with `absolute` when the same effect can be expressed as layered gradients on the container.
- Prefer container `background-image` gradients or borders over extra blurred DOM nodes for non-interactive decoration.
- Do not add full-screen decorative layers like `<div className="fixed inset-0 bg-gradient-...">` inside pages. Apply gradients directly on the page/container element instead.
- Only use `priority` on one true LCP image per page. Do not mark list, card, or repeated images as priority.
- Every non-fill image should provide stable dimensions and an appropriate `sizes` value.
- Prefer the local `components/Image.tsx` wrapper for project images so `BASE_PATH`, lazy loading, and default `sizes` stay consistent.

## Metadata and SEO

- Set `metadataBase` when returning metadata helpers or shared metadata objects.
- Keep canonical URLs and locale alternates stable after routing changes.
- After each completed implementation update, sync `app/[locale]/tools/{current}/seoData.ts` `LAST_MODIFIED_ISO` to current local datetime (include time component).

## Validation

- Run `yarn lint` and `yarn build` after Next-specific changes.
- For performance-sensitive UI work, verify affected mobile routes manually in dev mode.
